oviet Far East occurred in October 1953. The two exercises are similar in that fighter units were temporarily redeployed in regimental strength, usually to known bomber bases, and were noted operating from their temporary locations immediately following the moves.\n\nThis year larger numbers of aircraft and units are involved, more naval air units are participating, and for the first time there have been movements of jet light bombers from one field to another.\n\nComment: The stress on high unit mobility in this exercise may reflect continued Soviet emphasis on the role of air units in tactical support of ground forces. Frequent change-of-base exercises have been noted each year in the 24th Air Army in East Germany.\n\nFAR EAST\n\n3. Chinese Communist jet aircraft may be based at Liuchou:\n\nOn 23 March during an advanced training exercise by the Chinese Communist 26th Air Division, which is based at Liuchou in Kwangsi Province (see map, p. 5), referred to a landing approach speed of 178 knots. This suggests for the first time that jet planes may be operating from that base. The reporting unit adds that the 26th Air Division was previously known to have only a small number of conventional LA-11 and possibly LA-7 fighters.\n\nComment: The exercises were conducted on both 22 and 23 March and are the first advanced training noted to date, in the area. Previous activity was apparently limited to basic training.\n\nMeanwhile, it is estimated on the basis of photo reconnaissance that the Suichi airfield on Leichou Peninsula in South China can be completed by 15 May. This is the largest airfield in China, with a runway 10,000 feet long", "token_count": 276, "token_end_0based": 283, "token_start_0based": 8, "token_text": "the soviet far east occurred in october 1953 the two exercises are similar in that fighter units were temporarily redeployed in regimental strength usually to known bomber bases and were noted operating from their temporary locations immediately following the moves this year larger numbers of aircraft and units are involved more naval air units are participating and for the first time there have been movements of jet light bombers from one field to another comment the stress on high unit mobility in this exercise may reflect continued soviet emphasis on the role of air units in tactical support of ground forces frequent change-of-base exercises have been noted each year in the 24th air army in east germany far east 3 chinese communist jet aircraft may be based at liuchou on 23 march during an advanced training exercise by the chinese communist 26th air division which is based at liuchou in kwangsi province see map p 5 referred to a landing approach speed of 178 knots this suggests for the first time that jet planes may be operating from that base the reporting unit adds that the 26th air division was previously known to have only a small number of conventional la-11 and possibly la-7 fighters comment the exercises were conducted on both 22 and 23 march and are the first advanced training noted to date in the area previous activity was apparently limited to basic training meanwhile it is estimated on the basis of photo reconnaissance that the suichi airfield on leichou peninsula in south china can be completed by 15 may this is the largest airfield in china with a runway 10 000 feet long", "unred_source_page": 4}
